          "text": "negotiate with landlords = 與業主談判\nExample: A café owner must negotiate with landlords.\n（咖啡店老闆必須與業主談判。）\nAnalysis: This is a realistic business skill.\n\nmanage staff = 管理員工\nExample: A café owner must manage staff.\n（咖啡店老闆必須管理員工。）\nAnalysis: This transfers directly from workplace management to entrepreneurship.\n\ncontrol costs = 控制成本\nExample: A café owner must control costs.\n（咖啡店老闆必須控制成本。）\nAnalysis: Essential financial vocabulary.\n\nrespond to bad reviews = 回應差評\nExample: A café owner must respond to bad reviews.\n（咖啡店老闆必須回應差評。）\nAnalysis: This phrase reflects modern customer-service reality.\n\ndesign promotions = 設計促銷活動\nExample: A café owner must design promotions.\n（咖啡店老闆必須設計促銷活動。）\nAnalysis: This belongs to marketing vocabulary.\n\nstay calm = 保持冷靜\nExample: A café owner must stay calm when the espresso machine breaks down.\n（當咖啡機壞掉時，咖啡店老闆必須保持冷靜。）\nAnalysis: This phrase shows emotional management under pressure.\n\nduring the lunch rush = 午餐繁忙時段\nExample: When the espresso machine breaks down during the lunch rush.\n（當咖啡機在午餐繁忙時段壞掉。）\nAnalysis: This detail makes the operational stress vivid.\n\ndaily survival = 每日生存；日常營運求存\nExample: These are not dreamy tasks; they are daily survival.\n（這些不是夢幻任務；它們是每日生存。）\nAnalysis: This contrast is central to the essay’s realistic message.\n\nlisten, decide and act under pressure = 在壓力下聆聽、決定和行動\nExample: The company might teach you how to listen, decide and act under pressure.\n（公司可能教會你如何在壓力下聆聽、決定和行動。）\nAnalysis: The three verbs form a strong leadership sequence."
